The ideas that I learned in class that will most stick with me are:
 1. Students come to the classroom with misunderstandings about the material that I am planning to teach them. Their misconceptions effect their current understanding. So if I want students to change their understanding, then I must find out what their misconceptions are and address them directly.
 2. If I want my students to remember information, then it is important that they can encode than information, retain it, and also retrieve it when they need it. 
 3. When using technology in my classroom, I will aim to use it in ways that will not only enhance learning, but rather transform learning. Thus, I want to see if I can use technology in ways that will modify and redefine the tasks that I am already doing in my classroom. 
 4. Knowledge is different than understanding. I want to promote understanding in my classroom, but I need to realize that understanding takes time.
